	<div class='patients-container'>
		<h1>Do I need to visit a "foot doctor"?</h1>
		<div class='col-md-6 content-section'>
			<p>Our feet support our whole weight as we move, walk and run throughout the whole day. People often overlook the importance of healthy feet until theyâ€™ve experienced foot problems and we find that patients often too long before making an apointment</p>
			<h2>Our feet, those poor soles, are often taken for granted.</h2>
			<p>Further more, our footware makes a huge difference; wearing well-fitted shoes or orthodics versus shoving them into another pair of [beautiful] heels can greatly affect the health and comfort of your feet.</p> 
			<h2>Foot pain is not normal.</h2> 
			<p>If you have persistent pain or irritation, don't try to "walk it off." Foot pain can be chronic or acute and the fact that it supports your whole body means a variety of potential conditions can arise that can affect other body parts and overall health.</p>
			<h2>You should see a podiatrist if:</h2>
			<ul id="symptoms-links">
	            <li><%= link_to 'If you have pain, tenderness along the tendon', conditions_achilles_path %></li>
	            <li><%= link_to 'Pain, swelling, inflammation and stiffness', conditions_arthritis_path %>  Especially if it gets worse while running or being in colder or damper weather.</li>
	            <li><%= link_to 'If you have any painful or sensative growths.', conditions_bunion_path %> Common foot problems can also stem from wearing high heels and pointy shoes.</li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Thickening of skin that repeatedly gets rubbed by shoes causing calluses', conditions_callus_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Redness, drainage, swelling, bad odor, rash, or discoloration.', conditions_diabetic_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Leg weakness, pain in the feet and legs consisting of tingling, burning, or numbness', conditions_neuropathy_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Flattening of the arch or tendency to roll your ankle inward', conditions_flatfeet_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'If your foot is swollen, red, hot, bruised, or has changed in size, shape, or direction, see your foot and ankle surgeon immediately', conditions_fractures_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'If you twist your ankle or have any bruising', conditions_sprain_path %> (don't attempt to "walk it of\" as it can make things worse)</li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Soreness or bumps developing due to poor footwear', conditions_hammertoes_path %>  There is no amount of pain worth a fraction of "beauty".</li>
				<li><%= link_to 'Foot pain that feels worse first thing in the morning or after prolonged standing and walking', conditions_spur_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'When your toenails start to grow in way that causes pain, redness, swelling or sensitivity.', conditions_ingrown_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'If toenails start to discolor, thicken, or split.', conditions_fungus_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'If it feels like you are constantly \"walking on a pebble\"', conditions_neuroma_path %> or have burning, numbness, tingling, or pain in the ball of the foot.</li>
				<li><%= link_to 'If you want to have custom insoles made to reduce foot stress and pain', conditions_orthodics_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'If you notice clusters or layers of skin that are irritating and uncomfortable', conditions_wart_path %></li>
				<li><%= link_to 'If you have wounds or cuts on your foot that don\'t seem to be healing quickly.', conditions_wound_path %></li>
			</ul>
			<p><%= link_to 'Dr. Yoshida is happy to discuss your concerns', contact_path %>, and believes that quality patient care is of utmost importance.</p>

		</div>
